+- Closure stance therefore tightens rather than loosens: the audit is still safe for scoped, evidence-anchored fixes, but closure cannot be claimed while credentialed live parity is blocked and two closure-critical pass families still have only non-creditable completed labels instead of durable outputs.
+- Current credible follow-on order is: rerun `script-behavior-pass` with a durable report, rerun `same-student-cross-surface-parity-pass` with explicit blocked/live evidence, continue telemetry/startup + remaining frontend/helper-service mapping, then rerun credentialed `live-behavior-pass`.

